---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Press
description: Quote-me-as block, bios at three lengths, press log, recognitions, portrait kit.
---
<article>
  <header>
    <p class="eyebrow">Press</p>
    <h1>Press kit.</h1>
    <p class="lede">For interviews, citations, and reuse. Email <a href="mailto:{{ site.email.media }}">{{ site.email.media }}</a> for anything not on this page.</p>
  </header>

  <section aria-labelledby="quote">
    <h2 id="quote">Quote me as</h2>
    <p class="muted">Each line is the right one for a context. Pick the one that fits and copy it as-is.</p>
    <ul class="quote-block" id="quoteme">
      {% for line in quoteme %}
        <li>
          <span data-quote>{{ line }}</span>
          <button type="button" class="copy" data-copy aria-label="Copy line {{ loop.index }}">Copy</button>
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
    <p class="muted">When a publication needs an institutional anchor, the fifth (two-sentence) form supplies one. Independent work first, employer second; never inverted.</p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="bios">
    <h2 id="bios">Bios — three lengths</h2>
    <div class="bio-block">
      <details open>
        <summary>Short (≤ 40 words)</summary>
        <div class="bio-body" data-quote>
          <p>{{ bios.short }}</p>
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="copy" data-copy-target="prev">Copy</button>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Medium (≤ 110 words)</summary>
        <div class="bio-body" data-quote>
          <p>{{ bios.medium }}</p>
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="copy" data-copy-target="prev">Copy</button>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Long (≤ 240 words)</summary>
        <div class="bio-body" data-quote>
          {% for p in bios.long.split("\n\n") %}<p>{{ p }}</p>{% endfor %}
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="copy" data-copy-target="prev">Copy</button>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="portraits">
    <h2 id="portraits">Portraits</h2>
    <p class="muted">Square portrait, head-and-shoulders, dark backdrop. Reproduce with credit. Higher-resolution print files on request via media@anivar.net.</p>
    <figure class="portrait">
      {% portrait "anivar.jpg", "Anivar A. Aravind, head-and-shoulders portrait." %}
      <figcaption>Web display, ≤ 480px. Photographer credit pending — request the file at <a href="mailto:{{ site.email.media }}">media@anivar.net</a>.</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="recog">
    <h2 id="recog">Recognitions, standards, and fellowships</h2>
    <ul class="log-list">
      {% for r in log | byKinds('award,standard,fellowship,contribution') %}
        <li>
          <span class="badge badge-{{ r.kind }}">{{ r.kind | kindLabel }}</span>
          <span class="entry">
            <span class="title">{{ r.title }}{% if r.org %} — {{ r.org }}{% endif %}</span>
            {% if r.blurb %}<span class="blurb">{{ r.blurb }}</span>{% endif %}
          </span>
          <span class="when">{{ r | spanLabel }}</span>
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
    <p class="muted"><a href="/history/">Full chronology →</a></p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="log">
    <h2 id="log">Press log</h2>
    <p class="muted">Rebuild from the 2022 <code>/press/</code> archive in progress; recent items will land here with original publication dates and links. Historical clippings preserve their original employer attribution verbatim — those are quotes of the publication, not current self-description.</p>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="recommendations">
    <h2 id="recommendations">Selected recommendations</h2>
    <p class="muted">Excerpts from LinkedIn recommendations available on request via <a href="mailto:{{ site.email.media }}">media@anivar.net</a>. Will appear here as the user approves quotation.</p>
  </section>
</article>

<script src="/assets/js/copy.js" defer></script>
